  "datePublished": "2026-03-04",
  "description": "A keyword is a term or short phrase assigned to a piece of content to describe its subject matter for the purpose of indexing and discovery. Keywords serve a similar function to tags but carry a connotation of curation and restraint: where tags in a folksonomy are applied freely and in unlimited quantity, keywords in academic and publishing contexts are selected deliberately, limited in number (typically three to five, rarely more than ten), and expected to precisely characterize the work\u0026rsquo;s contribution to its field.\n",
